<subSubSection id="C33591857342387EFF5D9407FE57FB7A" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B90C20E7342387AFF5D9407FE03F835" blockId="3.[136,1452,1824,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
Diagnosis:—differing from the phylogenetically and morphologically closest related species 
<taxonomicName id="4C2FB98D7342387AFB599406FAEEF88D" box="[1164,1284,1824,1850]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Tricholomataceae" genus="Bonomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="arnoldii">
<emphasis id="B95B1E1C7342387AFB599406FAEEF88D" box="[1164,1284,1824,1850]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">B. arnoldii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its crowded lamellae, absence of granules at the top of the stipe, well-differentiated mediostratum and stipitipellis, genetic profile, and distribution in north 
<collectingCountry id="F338829E7342387AFE4A944FFE0CF835" box="[415,486,1896,1922]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B90C20E7342387AFF6894ABFBA0F811" blockId="3.[136,1452,1824,2031]" box="[189,1098,1932,1959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
Etymology:—‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2FB98D7342387AFEB294ABFDFBF811" authorityName="L. Fan &amp; N. Mao" authorityYear="2022" box="[359,529,1932,1958]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Tricholomataceae" genus="Bonomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pseudoarnoldii">
<emphasis id="B95B1E1C7342387AFEB294ABFDFBF811" box="[359,529,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">pseudoarnoldii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, refers to this species being similar to 
<emphasis id="B95B1E1C7342387AFC1C94AAFBA0F811" box="[969,1098,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName id="4C2FB98D7342387AFC1C94AAFBACF811" box="[969,1094,1932,1958]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Tricholomataceae" genus="Bonomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="arnoldii">B. arnoldii</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
